description: Look at the cables for any sign of damage, outcome='NOMINAL\n\nAll observed cables show no signs of visible damage or internal faults. Each cable is reported as connected where visible, or the connection status is hidden when the cable terminates inside an enclosure (Control Cube or Load Cube). No ruptures or other anomalies have been detected during the visual inspection.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Cables,
description: Test voltage polarity at the end of the control module, outcome="ANOMALOUS\n\nFeedback:\nThe voltages measured at both the positive and negative terminals of the control module's output are nearly identical (0.3592 V at 'ctrl_cable_out_pos' and 0.0003 V at 'ctrl_cable_out_neg', both w.r.t. ground). Normally, you would expect to see the positive terminal at a significantly higher voltage than the negative or ground terminal, indicating correct polarity.\n\nThis result can suggest the possibility of the problem ['CablesInverted'] (i.e., control cables may be inverted, causing unexpected voltage readings and polarity issues), or there may be a loss of expected supply voltage. Further investigation into the wiring and upstream voltage source is recommended.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> MainLoad,
description: Look at the lamp for any sign of damage or improper installation., outcome="NOMINAL\n\nBased on the visual inspection of the 'Main Load (lamp)', no internal faults were observed and there was no sign of damage or improper installation. The bulb is currently not lit, but this alone does not indicate the presence of 'BurnedFilaments' unless corroborated by further evidence. No anomalous behaviors suggesting 'BurnedFilaments' were detected at this stage.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=10.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
